F=\frac{T_{2}}{5}
[/latex] and

[latex]
\frac{T_{1}}{T_{2}}=e^{\mu \theta}
[/latex] [latex]
\frac{1500}{T_{2}}=e^{0.3 \times \pi}
[/latex] [latex]
\mathrm{T}_{2}=584.492 \mathrm{~N}
[/latex] So,

[latex]
\begin{aligned}
\mathrm{F} & =\frac{\mathrm{T}_{2}}{5}=\frac{584.432}{5} \\
& =116.9 \mathrm{~N} \approx 117 \mathrm{~N}
\end{aligned}
[/latex]

[latex]
\mathrm{L}=\left(\frac{\mathrm{C}}{\mathrm{P}}\right)^{\mathrm{n}} \times 10^{6} \mathrm{rev}
[/latex] [latex]\mathrm{n}=3[/latex] for ball bearing [latex]n=10 / 3[/latex] for roller bearing

[latex]
